(4) Conductors with white or gray insulation and colored tracer threads in the braid identifying the source of manufacture. (5) A single-conductor, sunlight-resistant, outdoor-rated cable used as a solidly grounded conductor in photovoltaic power systems, as permitted by 690.31 (C) (1), shall be identified at the time of installation by markings at terminations in accordance with 200.6 (A) (1) through (A) (4). (6) The grounded conductor of a mineral-insulated, metal-sheathed cable (Type MI) shall be identified at the time of installation by a distinctive white or gray marking at its terminations The marking shall encircle the conductor insulation.
